about.summary: A flexible, feature-rich yet light-weight logging framework based on 'R6' classes. It supports hierarchical loggers, custom log levels, arbitrary data fields in log events, logging to plaintext, 'JSON', (rotating) files, memory buffers, and databases, as well as email and push notifications. For a full list of features with examples please refer to the package vignette.

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.4.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-lgr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/lgr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/lgr/lgr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 8c55b2d81cfe8b80f0c42f28f31d77d9f1eb9b3fe78839cd1877c3a93c1649a3

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-r6 >=2.4.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-r6 >=2.4.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('lgr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('lgr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://s-fleck.github.io/lgr
  license: MIT
  summary: A flexible, feature-rich yet light-weight logging framework based on 'R6' classes. It supports hierarchical loggers, custom log levels, arbitrary data fields in log events, logging to plaintext, 'JSON', (rotating) files, memory buffers, and databases, as well as email and push notifications. For a full list of
    features with examples please refer to the package vignette.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
